---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="The network"
  description="FlyItalyADSB's receiver network: a global grid of feeders augmented by adsb.lol and theairtraffic.com, with MLAT active over Italy."
>
  <div class="pt-24 pb-20 px-6 sm:px-12 lg:px-20 max-w-7xl mx-auto">

    <div class="mb-14">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Infrastructure</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-slate-100 mb-4">The network</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-400 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        FlyItalyADSB aggregates data from a worldwide network of private receivers
        and international aggregation networks. The result is global ADS-B coverage
        with high density over Italy and the Mediterranean, and the only active MLAT service over Italy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Architecture -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-16">

      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border" style="background:#0f1929;border-color:#1e3048">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background:#38bdf815;border:1px solid #38bdf830">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#38bdf8" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path d="M3 12a9 9 0 1 0 18 0 9 9 0 0 0-18 0" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <path d="M3 12h18M12 3a15 15 0 0 1 0 18M12 3a15 15 0 0 0 0 18" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-100">Our receiver network</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Private receivers contributed by community members across Italy and beyond.
          Coverage extends from the Alps to Sicily, from the Tyrrhenian Sea to the Adriatic coast,
          with individual antennas reaching up to 400 km. Together they form the densest
          ground-truth ADS-B network over Italy.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-xs">
          <div class="flex justify-between py-1 border-b" style="border-color:#1e3048">
            <span class="text-slate-500">Input protocol</span>
            <span class="text-slate-300 font-mono">BEAST TCP · port 4905</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between py-1 border-b" style="border-color:#1e3048">
            <span class="text-slate-500">Mode-S EHS</span>
            <span class="text-slate-300 font-mono">BDS50 · BDS60 · BDS44</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between py-1">
            <span class="text-slate-500">MLAT</span>
            <span class="text-slate-300 font-mono">port 30100</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border" style="background:#0f1929;border-color:#1e3048">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center" style="background:#38bdf815;border:1px solid #38bdf830">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#38bdf8" stroke-width="1.5">
              <path d="M21 16V8a2 2 0 0 0-1-1.73l-7-4a2 2 0 0 0-2 0l-7 4A2 2 0 0 0 3 8v8a2 2 0 0 0 1 1.73l7 4a2 2 0 0 0 2 0l7-4A2 2 0 0 0 21 16z" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h2 class="font-semibold text-slate-100">International aggregators</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The readsb-globe server connects to <strong class="text-slate-300">adsb.lol</strong> and
          <strong class="text-slate-300">theairtraffic.com</strong> to aggregate global feeds.
          This extends coverage worldwide, with MLAT data from these networks
          merged into the local aggregated stream.
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-2 text-xs">
          <div class="flex justify-between py-1 border-b" style="border-color:#1e3048">
            <span class="text-slate-500">adsb.lol</span>
            <span class="text-slate-300 font-mono">BEAST in · SBS MLAT in</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between py-1 border-b" style="border-color:#1e3048">
            <span class="text-slate-500">theairtraffic.com</span>
            <span class="text-slate-300 font-mono">BEAST in · SBS MLAT in</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between py-1">
            <span class="text-slate-500">OGN (light aircraft)</span>
            <span class="text-slate-300 font-mono">FLARM/FANET → SBS</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Pipeline -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-8">Data pipeline</p>
      <div class="relative">
        <div class="absolute left-5 top-8 bottom-8 w-px" style="background:linear-gradient(to bottom, #38bdf830, #38bdf810)"></div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            { step: '01', title: 'Ingestion', desc: 'Feeders send BEAST TCP data to readsb-ingest (port 4905). Simultaneously, readsb-globe receives from adsb.lol and theairtraffic.com.', tags: ['readsb-ingest', 'readsb-globe'] },
            { step: '02', title: 'MLAT', desc: 'MLAT clients (port 30100) send time-stamped measurements to mlat-server. With at least 4 synchronized receivers, the server triangulates aircraft position without GPS.', tags: ['mlat-server', 'port 30100'] },
            { step: '03', title: 'Aggregation', desc: 'readsb-globe merges all feeds: local feeders, computed MLAT, adsb.lol, theairtraffic.com, OGN. Outputs aircraft.json every 200ms and updates heatmap history.', tags: ['aircraft.json', '0.2s', 'heatmap'] },
            { step: '04', title: 'Distribution', desc: 'Data is served to the tar1090 map via local Unix socket, to the MyFlyItalyADSB dashboard via PostgreSQL, and used by the weather-32 meteorological pipeline.', tags: ['tar1090', 'my.flyitalyadsb.com', 'weather-32'] },
          ].map(item => (
            <div class="flex gap-6 pl-12 relative">
              <div class="absolute left-0 top-4 w-10 h-10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-mono font-bold shrink-0"
                   style="background:#0f1929;border:1px solid #38bdf830;color:#38bdf8">{item.step}</div>
              <div class="flex-1 p-5 rounded-xl border" style="background:#0f1929;border-color:#1e3048">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-100 mb-1">{item.title}</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">{item.desc}</p>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                  {item.tags.map(tag => <span class="text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-mono" style="background:#111e30;color:#64748b">{tag}</span>)}
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl p-8 border flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 items-center"
         style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0f1929 0%,#111e30 100%);border-color:#1e3048">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-100 text-xl mb-2">Add your receiver</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">More receivers mean better MLAT coverage and denser Mode-S data for meteorological research.</p>
      </div>
      <a href="/en/community/feeder"
         class="shrink-0 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium text-sm no-underline transition-all"
         style="background:#38bdf8;color:#070d1a"
         onmouseover="this.style.background='#7dd3fc'"
         onmouseout="this.style.background='#38bdf8'">
        Become a feeder →
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
